"{\"uid\": \"countrylife.co.uk-nature-sir-peter-scott-the-olympic-sailor-national-glider-flying-champion-and-second-world-war-veteran-who-became-the-father-of-wildfowl-conservation-269153\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"As well as helping found the WWF and designing its panda logo, he also took part in a hunt to find the Loch Ness Monster.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29, \"end\": 32, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.672680389480148e-23, \"text\": \"WWF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\"}, {\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.538053159466009e-51, \"text\": \"Loch Ness Monster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its panda logo\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 80}, {\"ngram\": \"a hunt\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 90}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Make the boy interested in natural history if you can\\u2026 Guard him against indolence,' wrote Capt Robert Scott in his last letter to his wife.\", \"from\": 123, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 219, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Falcon_Scott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.631204906180211e-32, \"text\": \"Robert Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Falcon_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Falcon_Scott\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the boy\", \"from\": 128, \"to\": 135}, {\"ngram\": \"natural history\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 165}, {\"ngram\": \"indolence\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"his last letter\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 250}, {\"ngram\": \"his wife\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peter Scott (1909-89) was only two when his father perished in Antarctica in 1912, but that small boy grew up to engender a worldwide conservation movement, as well as being a writer (he was first published by Country Life) and artist of note.\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 264, \"end\": 275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Scott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2600549942114812e-74, \"text\": \"Peter Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 474, \"end\": 486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Country_Life_in_America\", \"score\": 0.9999871455387082, \"rank\": 1.2854626362269837e-05, \"text\": \"Country Life\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Country_Life_in_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Country_Life_in_America\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his father\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"Antarctica\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 337}, {\"ngram\": \"that small boy\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"a worldwide conservation movement\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 419}, {\"ngram\": \"a writer\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"artist\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"note\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sir Peter (he was the first Briton to be knighted for services to conservation) was good at pretty much everything: he was the first president of the Society of Wildlife Artists, he won an Olympic bronze medal for sailing in 1936, he was a national glider-flying champion and was decorated in the Second World War.\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first Briton\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"services\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 571}, {\"ngram\": \"conservation\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"pretty much everything\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"the first president\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"the Society\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"Wildlife Artists\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic bronze medal\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"sailing\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"a national glider-flying champion\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"the Second World War\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was also a good wildfowling shot, describing the call of the shore inMorning Flight(1935), and was enthralled by the migrant geese arriving in the Fens - 'Like a symphony of Beethoven, their call is everlasting' - but, in the early 1930s, a bag of some 80 pink-footed geese proved a Damascene moment: 'The species can ill afford to lose so many individuals,' he concluded.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pink-footed_goose\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"pink-footed geese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pink-footed_goose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pink-footed_goose\"}, {\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conversion_of_Paul_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.7615168687245943, \"rank\": 0.18813001029610163, \"text\": \"Damascene\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conversion_of_Paul_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conversion_of_Paul_the_Apostle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good wildfowling shot\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the call\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the Fens\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"a symphony\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"Beethoven\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"their call\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"the early 1930s\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"a bag\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"The species\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"so many individuals\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1946, he founded the Wildfowl and Wetland Trust, with its headquarters at Slimbridge, Gloucestershire, where it remains; he helped instigate the World Wildlife Fund, designing its panda logo; is credited with saving the Hawaiian (nene) goose from extinction; and discovered from drawing Bewick swans that they had unique beak patterns.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wetland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wetland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wetland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wetland\"}, {\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Wildlife Fund\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Wide_Fund_for_Nature\"}, {\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\", \"score\": 0.9998528047125794, \"rank\": 9.316882220625696e-05, \"text\": \"Hawaiian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaiian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Wildfowl\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"its headquarters\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"Slimbridge\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"Gloucestershire\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"its panda logo\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"extinction\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"Bewick swans\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"unique beak patterns\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This method of identifying returning birds to Slimbridge is still used 10,000 swans and 60 years later.\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slimbridge\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0500536980874629e-11, \"text\": \"Slimbridge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slimbridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slimbridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This method\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"returning birds\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"10,000 swans\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also conducted extensive research into the existence of the Loch Ness Monster.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.538053159466009e-51, \"text\": \"Loch Ness Monster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loch_Ness_Monster\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"extensive research\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"the existence\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1961, Sir Peter joined a group convinced that it was worth looking into the existence of 'Nessie'.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Pan\", \"score\": 0.9839151429729077, \"rank\": 0.01583130483078029, \"text\": 